{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GSehz79K7Mz1dqjwe8JwFt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<persistence version=\"3.0\" xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/persistence/persistence_3_0.xsd\">\n    16→  <persistence-unit name=\"order\" transaction-type=\"JTA\">\n    17→    <jta-data-source>java:comp/DefaultDataSource</jta-data-source>\n    18→    <properties>\n    19→      <property name=\"jakarta.persistence.schema-generation.database.action\" value=\"drop-and-create\"/>\n    20→      <property name=\"eclipselink.ddl-generation.output-mode\" value=\"both\"/>\n    21→      <property name=\"eclipselink.logging.level.sql\" value=\"FINE\"/>\n    22→      <property name=\"eclipselink.logging.level\" value=\"INFO\"/>\n    23→    </properties>\n    24→  </persistence-unit>\n    25→</persistence>\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"6f1336f9-2ed5-44b5-b2f6-5afd92ff3cd5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QXvHqFUtF74BJuioStZEuz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<web-app version=\"5.0\"\n    16→         xmlns=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee\" \n    17→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" \n    18→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee https://jakarta.ee/xml/ns/jakartaee/web-app_5_0.xsd\">\n    19→  <context-param>\n    20→        <param-name>jakarta.faces.PROJECT_STAGE</param-name>\n    21→        <param-value>Development</param-value>\n    22→    </context-param>\n    23→    <servlet>\n    24→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    25→        <servlet-class>\n    26→            jakarta.faces.webapp.FacesServlet\n    27→        </servlet-class>\n    28→        <load-on-startup>1</load-on-startup>\n    29→    </servlet>\n    30→    <servlet-mapping>\n    31→        <servlet-name>Faces Servlet</servlet-name>\n    32→        <url-pattern>*.xhtml</url-pattern>\n    33→    </servlet-mapping>\n    34→    <session-config>\n    35→        <session-timeout>30</session-timeout>\n    36→    </session-config>\n    37→   <welcome-file-list>\n    38→     <welcome-file>order.xhtml</welcome-file>\n    39→   </welcome-file-list>\n    40→</web-app>\n    41→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"89a15f8d-2f23-4989-84ba-98fd20d5cc56"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JkgqZNPVFpxsW5AKLwUbJr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n     2→<server description=\"Address Book on Open Liberty\">\n     3→\n     4→    <featureManager>\n     5→        <feature>jakartaee-10.0</feature>\n     6→    </featureManager>\n     7→\n     8→    <httpEndpoint id=\"defaultHttpEndpoint\" host=\"*\" httpPort=\"9080\" httpsPort=\"9443\" />\n     9→\n    10→    <basicRegistry id=\"basic\" realm=\"BasicRealm\">\n    11→        <user name=\"admin\" password=\"admin\" />\n    12→    </basicRegistry>\n    13→\n    14→    <library id=\"h2Library\">\n    15→        <fileset dir=\"${shared.resource.dir}\" includes=\"h2*.jar\"/>\n    16→    </library>\n    17→\n    18→    <dataSource id=\"DefaultDataSource\" jndiName=\"jdbc/DefaultDataSource\">\n    19→        <jdbcDriver libraryRef=\"h2Library\" javax.sql.DataSource=\"org.h2.jdbcx.JdbcDataSource\" />\n    20→        <properties url=\"jdbc:h2:mem:addressbook\" />\n    21→    </dataSource>\n    22→\n    23→</server>\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"8a07d8c9-13b6-4257-afce-3c0160ab5164"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QSq3gMXqBAPuYC8Ve7NXPu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' ?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n    16→<html lang=\"en\"\n    17→      xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n    18→      xmlns:f=\"jakarta.faces.core\"\n    19→      xmlns:h=\"jakarta.faces.html\"\n    20→      xmlns:ui=\"jakarta.faces.facelets\">\n    21→    <ui:composition template=\"/order-template.xhtml\">\n    22→        <ui:define name=\"title\">Order Java Persistence Example</ui:define>\n    23→        <ui:define name=\"body\">\n    24→\n    25→        </ui:define>\n    26→\n    27→        <ui:define name=\"ordersTable\">\n    28→\n    29→            <h:dataTable\n    30→                var=\"order\"\n    31→                summary=\"Table of orders\"\n    32→                value=\"#{orderManager.orders}\"\n    33→                rules=\"all\"\n    34→                cellpadding=\"5\">\n    35→                <h:column>\n    36→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    37→                        <h:outputText value=\"Order ID\" />\n    38→                    </f:facet>\n    39→                    <h:form>\n    40→                        <h:commandLink id=\"order_id_link\" action=\"lineItem\">\n    41→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{order.orderId}\" />\n    42→                            <f:setPropertyActionListener target=\"#{orderManager.currentOrder}\" value=\"#{order.orderId}\" />\n    43→                        </h:commandLink>\n    44→                    </h:form>\n    45→                </h:column>\n    46→                <h:column>\n    47→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    48→                        <h:outputText value=\"Shipment Info\" />\n    49→                    </f:facet>\n    50→                    <h:outputText value=\"#{order.shipmentInfo}\" />\n    51→                </h:column>\n    52→                <h:column>\n    53→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    54→                        <h:outputText value=\"Status\" />\n    55→                    </f:facet>\n    56→                    <h:outputText value=\"#{order.status}\" />\n    57→                </h:column>\n    58→                <h:column>\n    59→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    60→                        <h:outputText value=\"Last Updated\" />\n    61→                    </f:facet>\n    62→                    <h:outputText value=\"#{order.lastUpdate}\" />\n    63→                </h:column>\n    64→                <h:column>\n    65→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    66→                        <h:outputText value=\"Discount\" />\n    67→                    </f:facet>\n    68→                    <h:outputText value=\"#{order.discount}%\" />\n    69→                </h:column>\n    70→                <h:column>\n    71→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    72→                        <h:outputText value=\"Actions\" />\n    73→                    </f:facet>\n    74→                    <h:form>\n    75→                        <h:commandLink value=\"Delete\" actionListener=\"#{orderManager.removeOrder}\" action=\"order\">\n    76→                            <f:param name=\"deleteOrderId\" id=\"deleteOrderId\" value=\"#{order.orderId}\" />\n    77→                        </h:commandLink>\n    78→                    </h:form>\n    79→                </h:column>\n    80→            </h:dataTable>\n    81→        </ui:define>\n    82→\n    83→        <ui:define name=\"newOrderForm\">\n    84→            <h:form>\n    85→                <h:outputLabel for=\"orderIdInputText\" rendered=\"true\" value=\"Order ID: \" />\n    86→                <h:inputText id=\"orderIdInputText\" required=\"true\" value=\"#{orderManager.newOrderId}\" /><br />\n    87→\n    88→\n    89→                <h:outputLabel for=\"shipmentInfoInputText\" rendered=\"true\" value=\"Shipment Info: \" />\n    90→                <h:inputText id=\"shipmentInfoInputText\" required=\"true\" value=\"#{orderManager.newOrderShippingInfo}\" /><br />\n    91→\n    92→                <h:outputLabel for=\"statusMenu\" rendered=\"true\" value=\"Status: \" />\n    93→                <h:selectOneMenu id=\"statusMenu\" required=\"true\" value=\"#{orderManager.newOrderStatus}\">\n    94→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"Y\" itemLabel=\"Complete\" />\n    95→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"N\" itemLabel=\"Pending\" />\n    96→                </h:selectOneMenu><br />\n    97→\n    98→                <h:outputLabel for=\"discountMenu\" rendered=\"true\" value=\"Discount: \" />\n    99→                <h:selectOneMenu id=\"discountMenu\" required=\"true\" value=\"#{orderManager.newOrderDiscount}\">\n   100→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"0\" itemLabel=\"0 %\" />\n   101→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"5\" itemLabel=\"5 %\" />\n   102→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"10\" itemLabel=\"10 %\" />\n   103→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"15\" itemLabel=\"15 %\" />\n   104→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"20\" itemLabel=\"20 %\" />\n   105→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"25\" itemLabel=\"25 %\" />\n   106→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"30\" itemLabel=\"30 %\" />\n   107→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"35\" itemLabel=\"35 %\" />\n   108→                    <f:selectItem itemValue=\"40\" itemLabel=\"40 %\" />\n   109→                </h:selectOneMenu><br />\n   110→\n   111→                <h:commandButton value=\"Submit\" action=\"#{orderManager.submitOrder}\" />\n   112→            </h:form>\n   113→\n   114→        </ui:define>\n   115→\n   116→        <ui:define name=\"findVendorForm\">\n   117→            <h:form>\n   118→                <h:outputLabel for=\"findVendorInputText\" rendered=\"true\" value=\"Search for Vendors: \" />\n   119→                <h:inputText id=\"findVendorInputText\" value=\"#{orderManager.vendorName}\" required=\"true\" />\n   120→                <h:commandButton id=\"findVendorButton\" action=\"#{orderManager.findVendor}\" value=\"Find Vendor\" />\n   121→            </h:form>\n   122→        </ui:define>\n   123→\n   124→        <ui:define name=\"findVendorTable\">\n   125→            <h:dataTable var=\"vendor\" \n   126→                         summary=\"Table of vendors\"\n   127→                         value=\"#{orderManager.vendorSearchResults}\"\n   128→                         rules=\"all\"\n   129→                         cellpadding=\"5\"\n   130→                         rendered=\"#{orderManager.findVendorTableDisabled}\">\n   131→                <h:column>\n   132→                    <f:facet name=\"header\">\n   133→                        <h:outputText value=\"Vendor\" />\n   134→                    </f:facet>\n   135→                    <h:outputText value=\"#{vendor}\" />\n   136→                </h:column>\n   137→            </h:dataTable>\n   138→\n   139→        </ui:define>\n   140→    </ui:composition>\n   141→</html>\n   142→\n   143→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"1f13f8f2-7524-4ece-8c78-f12b9aadb012"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01UqRPN8hwfA3sMsPCmMdiob","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' ?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n    16→<html lang=\"en\"\n    17→      xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n    18→      xmlns:ui=\"jakarta.faces.facelets\"\n    19→      xmlns:h=\"jakarta.faces.html\">\n    20→    <h:head>\n    21→        <title>Order JPA Example</title>\n    22→        <h:outputStylesheet library=\"css\" name=\"default.css\"/>\n    23→    </h:head>\n    24→    <body>\n    25→        <h1><ui:insert name=\"title\">Default Title</ui:insert></h1>\n    26→\n    27→        <ui:insert name=\"body\">Default Body</ui:insert>\n    28→\n    29→        <h2>View All Orders</h2>\n    30→        <ui:insert name=\"ordersTable\">Default ordersTable</ui:insert>\n    31→\n    32→        <h2>Create New Order</h2>\n    33→        <ui:insert name=\"newOrderForm\">Default new orders form</ui:insert>\n    34→\n    35→        <h2>Find Vendors</h2>\n    36→        <ui:insert name=\"findVendorForm\">Default find vendors form</ui:insert>\n    37→\n    38→        <ui:insert name=\"findVendorTable\">Default find vendor table</ui:insert>\n    39→    </body>\n    40→</html>\n    41→\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"31d58b89-724d-4b6a-b920-628cf49d4448"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KNQJe25d4tFaB1nS3edcBZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' ?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n    16→<html lang=\"en\"\n    17→      xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n    18→      xmlns:f=\"jakarta.faces.core\"\n    19→      xmlns:h=\"jakarta.faces.html\"\n    20→      xmlns:ui=\"jakarta.faces.facelets\">\n    21→        <ui:composition template=\"/lineItem-template.xhtml\">\n    22→\n    23→            <ui:define name=\"title\">Line Items for Order #{orderManager.currentOrder}</ui:define>\n    24→            <ui:define name=\"body\">\n    25→                <h:form>\n    26→                    <h:dataTable var=\"lineItem\"\n    27→                                 summary=\"Table of line items\"\n    28→                                 value=\"#{orderManager.lineItems}\"\n    29→                                 rules=\"all\"\n    30→                                 cellpadding=\"5\">\n    31→                        <h:column>\n    32→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    33→                                <h:outputText value=\"Item ID\" />\n    34→                            </f:facet>\n    35→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{lineItem.itemId}\" />\n    36→                        </h:column>\n    37→                        <h:column>\n    38→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    39→                                <h:outputText value=\"Quantity\" />\n    40→                            </f:facet>\n    41→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{lineItem.quantity}\" />\n    42→                        </h:column>\n    43→                        <h:column>\n    44→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    45→                                <h:outputText value=\"Vendor Part Number\" />\n    46→                            </f:facet>\n    47→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{lineItem.vendorPart.vendorPartNumber}\" />\n    48→                        </h:column>\n    49→                    </h:dataTable>\n    50→                    <br />\n    51→\n    52→                    <h:dataTable id=\"orderPartsTable\"\n    53→                                 summary=\"Table of parts\"\n    54→                                 value=\"#{orderManager.newOrderParts}\"\n    55→                                 var=\"part\"\n    56→                                 rules=\"all\"\n    57→                                 cellpadding=\"5\">\n    58→                        <h:column>\n    59→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    60→                                <h:outputText value=\"Part Number\" />\n    61→                            </f:facet>\n    62→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{part.partNumber}\" />\n    63→                        </h:column>\n    64→                        <h:column>\n    65→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    66→                                <h:outputText value=\"Revision\" />\n    67→                            </f:facet>\n    68→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{part.revision}\" />\n    69→                        </h:column>\n    70→                        <h:column>\n    71→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    72→                                <h:outputText value=\"Vendor Part Number\" />\n    73→                            </f:facet>\n    74→                            <h:outputText value=\"#{part.vendorPart.vendorPartNumber}\" />\n    75→                        </h:column>\n    76→                        <h:column>\n    77→                            <f:facet name=\"header\">\n    78→                                <h:outputText value=\"Add To Order\" />\n    79→                            </f:facet>\n    80→                            <h:commandButton value=\"Add\" action=\"#{orderManager.addLineItem}\">\n    81→                                <f:setPropertyActionListener target=\"#{orderManager.selectedPartNumber}\" value=\"#{part.partNumber}\" />\n    82→                                <f:setPropertyActionListener target=\"#{orderManager.selectedPartRevision}\" value=\"#{part.revision}\" />\n    83→                                <f:setPropertyActionListener target=\"#{orderManager.selectedVendorPartNumber}\" value=\"#{part.vendorPart.vendorPartNumber}\" />\n    84→                            </h:commandButton>\n    85→                        </h:column>\n    86→                    </h:dataTable>\n    87→                    <br />\n    88→\n    89→                    <h:commandButton value=\"Back To Orders\" action=\"order\" />\n    90→                </h:form>\n    91→            </ui:define>\n    92→\n    93→        </ui:composition>\n    94→</html>\n    95→\n    96→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"6504004a-afbb-45cb-9994-b01668bbd1f0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013toqhHu9Qam8wVeog4G3or","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8' ?>\n     2→<!--\n     3→\n     4→    Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     5→\n     6→    All rights reserved.\n     7→\n     8→    This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     9→    terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n    10→    https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n    11→\n    12→    SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    13→\n    14→-->\n    15→<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n    16→<html lang=\"en\"\n    17→      xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\n    18→      xmlns:ui=\"jakarta.faces.facelets\"\n    19→      xmlns:h=\"jakarta.faces.html\">\n    20→    <h:head>\n    21→        <title>Order Persistence Example</title>\n    22→        <h:outputStylesheet library=\"css\" name=\"default.css\"/>\n    23→    </h:head>\n    24→    <body>\n    25→        <h1><ui:insert name=\"title\">Default Title</ui:insert></h1>\n    26→\n    27→        <ui:insert name=\"body\">Default Body</ui:insert>\n    28→    </body>\n    29→</html>\n    30→\n    31→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"32c88f29-9d99-4b13-a5fb-c1ba74993cce"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FkPks9oA2br1vBUgTaa2jc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture of the application. Let me plan and execute the migration.\n\n**Analysis Summary:**\n- Jakarta EE 10 application with JSF (web UI), EJB (business logic), JPA (persistence), CDI\n- Open Liberty application server\n- H2 in-memory database\n- Complex entity model with orders, line items, parts, vendors\n\n**Migration Strategy:**\nThe JSF+EJB application needs to be converted to Quarkus with JAX-RS REST endpoints (since Quarkus doesn't support JSF/EJB). I'll:\n1. Keep JPA entities (jakarta.persistence is compatible with Quarkus)\n2. Replace EJBs with CDI beans + `@Transactional`\n3. Replace JSF web layer with JAX-RS REST endpoints\n4. Replace persistence.xml with Quarkus application.properties\n5. Add data initialization via `@Startup` CDI bean"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7502,"cache_read_input_tokens":41684,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7502,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":674},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"0b7976f9-2fe4-4599-b5f3-e55b402df524"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01FkPks9oA2br1vBUgTaa2jc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01NuK9ftsahfbcHqBkTRzQ9c","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Analyze existing codebase structure","status":"completed","activeForm":"Analyzing existing codebase structure"},{"content":"Create new pom.xml with Quarkus dependencies","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Creating new pom.xml with Quarkus dependencies"},{"content":"Create application.properties for Quarkus config","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating application.properties"},{"content":"Refactor entity classes for Quarkus compatibility","status":"pending","activeForm":"Refactoring entity classes"},{"content":"Convert EJB RequestBean to CDI @ApplicationScoped bean","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting RequestBean to CDI"},{"content":"Convert EJB ConfigBean to Quarkus startup bean","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting ConfigBean to startup bean"},{"content":"Replace JSF OrderManager with JAX-RS REST resources","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating JAX-RS REST resources"},{"content":"Remove obsolete files (Liberty config, JSF, web.xml)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Removing obsolete files"},{"content":"Update Dockerfile for Quarkus","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating Dockerfile"},{"content":"Create smoke tests","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating smoke tests"},{"content":"Build Docker image and test","status":"pending","activeForm":"Building and testing Docker image"},{"content":"Document in CHANGELOG.md","status":"pending","activeForm":"Documenting in CHANGELOG.md"}]}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7502,"cache_read_input_tokens":41684,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7502,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":674},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"977dd140-f906-4c0a-9f48-4fa4556b09e9"}
