{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01UAyoWGRQ54FHHLvbE6PHLN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting - some endpoints are returning wrapped objects and others seem to be returning nothing (lineItems/count is empty). The issue is that `Response.ok(avgPrice).build()` where `avgPrice` is a `Double` is being serialized as `{\"price\": ...}` by RESTEasy/Jackson. The `count` endpoint returns empty because an `int` via `Response.ok(count)` seems to cause issues.\n\nLet me fix the REST endpoints to return proper JSON-friendly responses. I'll use simple wrapper objects or return the values directly:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":294,"cache_read_input_tokens":137339,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":294,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":271},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"38038bf5-d2b8-434e-b761-a39bd1db32dc"}
