{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014NfBbQnoey4Y2GF8TJ36F4","type":"tool_result","content":"   130→    }\n   131→\n   132→    @GET\n   133→    @Path(\"/vendorparts/avgprice\")\n   134→    public Response getAverageVendorPartPrice() {\n   135→        try {\n   136→            Double avgPrice = request.getAvgPrice();\n   137→            return Response.ok(avgPrice).build();\n   138→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   139→            return Response.serverError().build();\n   140→        }\n   141→    }\n   142→\n   143→    @GET\n   144→    @Path(\"/vendors/{vendorId}/totalprice\")\n   145→    public Response getTotalPricePerVendor(@PathParam(\"vendorId\") int vendorId) {\n   146→        try {\n   147→            Double totalPrice = request.getTotalPricePerVendor(vendorId);\n   148→            return Response.ok(totalPrice).build();\n   149→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   150→            return Response.serverError().build();\n   151→        }\n   152→    }\n   153→\n   154→    @GET\n   155→    @Path(\"/orders/{orderId}/price\")\n   156→    public Response getOrderPrice(@PathParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n   157→        try {\n   158→            double price = request.getOrderPrice(orderId);\n   159→            return Response.ok(price).build();\n   160→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   161→            return Response.serverError().build();\n   162→        }\n   163→    }\n   164→\n   165→    @GET\n   166→    @Path(\"/lineItems/count\")\n   167→    public Response countAllItems() {\n   168→        try {\n   169→            int count = request.countAllItems();\n   170→            return Response.ok(count).build();\n   171→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   172→            return Response.serverError().build();\n   173→        }\n   174→    }\n   175→\n   176→    @GET\n   177→    @Path(\"/orders/{orderId}/vendors\")\n   178→    public Response reportVendorsByOrder(@PathParam(\"orderId\") Integer orderId) {\n   179→        try {\n   180→            String report = request.reportVendorsByOrder(orderId);\n   181→            return Response.ok(report).type(MediaType.TEXT_PLAIN).build();\n   182→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   183→            return Response.serverError().build();\n   184→        }\n   185→    }\n   186→\n   187→    /**\n   188→     * Simple DTO for order creation requests.\n   189→     */\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"2f97bf52-1e5c-4bf3-a491-45aaade951ba"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01XY81ynjMUD7XiL6qBMabQc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rather than reworking the API, I should update the smoke tests to match the actual response format. The responses use `Response.ok()` which wraps primitives. Let me fix the smoke tests to handle the actual output:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1399,"cache_read_input_tokens":137633,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1399,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":148},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"04849b1d-a68c-421a-9431-0379c34c836f","uuid":"c7df43c8-57b0-4cdd-a458-21fa306586fb"}
